<p>Indiana offers additional state-level incentives including property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase property tax bills. Indiana Michigan Power participates in net metering programs, allowing Fort Wayne customers to receive credit for excess solar energy fed back into the grid at the retail rate of 11.8¬¢/kWh. For HVAC systems, federal tax credits up to \$2,000 are available for qualifying high-efficiency heat pumps, while energy-efficient furnaces and air conditioners may qualify for manufacturer rebates up to \$1,200. Local contractors often provide additional incentives and financing options specifically for Fort Wayne residents.</p>

